15 (b) A local school system that offers the PSAT/NMSQT, SAT, PreACT, ACT, or Armed
16 Services Vocational Aptitude Battery (ASVAB) or an advanced placement exam to
17 students enrolled in such local school system shall:
18 (1) Make each such test or exam available to any home study student who would be
19 enrolled in such local school system by virtue of his or her residence under the same
20 rules, policies, and procedures for such test or exam that apply to students enrolled in
21 such local school system who are participating in such test or exam. Such test or exam
22 may be offered to such home study students at the same date and time that such test or
23 exam is offered to students enrolled in such local school system, or at another date and
24 time selected by such local school system; and
25 (2) Post on its public website notice of each such test or exam to be administered. Such
26 notice shall:
27 (A) Include each such test or exam date;
28 (B) Include registration deadlines and procedures; and
29 (C) State that such test or exam is available to home study students who would be
30 enrolled in such local school system by virtue of their residence.
31 (c) A local school system that offers the PSAT/NMSQT, SAT, PreACT, ACT, or Armed
32 Services Vocational Aptitude Battery (ASVAB) or an advanced placement exam to
33 students enrolled in such local school system shall not, as a condition of a home study
34 student participating in such test or exam:
35 (1) Impose any fee that is not imposed on students enrolled in such local school system;
36 or
37 (2) Impose any requirement that conflicts with or is in addition to the requirements of
38 subsection (c) of Code Section 20-2-690."
39 SECTION 2.
40 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
